m%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Evergreen%20Wealth%2C%20an%20RIA%20registered%20investment%20advisory.%20We%20provide%20our%20largely%20high-net-worth%20clients%20with%20investment%20management%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-wealth-building-strategies-financial-independence-fire-real-estate-leverage-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20using%20AI%20to%20enhance%20our%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20a%20decade%20in%20media%20in%20New%20York%20and%20then%20a%20decade%20in%20corporate%20fintech%20in%20California%2C%20where%20I%20served%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20PayPal%20and%20Intuit%20(now%20TurboTax).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20I%20spent%20a%2025-year%20stint%20in%20fintech%20startups%2C%20with%20seven%20successes%20and%20two%20failures%2C%20all%20of%20which%20ultimately%20led%20to%20Evergreen%20Wealth%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimplicity%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20to%20me.%20When%20I%20was%20married%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-parents-raising-their-kids-tech-free-red-flag-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eraising%20kids%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20days%20were%20a%20jumble%20of%20competing%20obligations.%20Now%2C%20I%20live%20alone%20in%20a%201%2C200-square-foot%20cottage%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-miami-instead-bay-area-tech-career-right-choice-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMiami%20Beach%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20no%20car.%20The%20simplicity%20of%20not%20having%20anything%20else%20that%20commands%20my%20attention%20is%20remarkably%20liberating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20I'm%2069%2C%20I%20haven't%20retired%20because%20this%20remains%20the%20most%20engaging%20thing%20I%20do.%20If%20and%20when%20I%20retire%2C%20I%20plan%20to%20attend%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20as%20a%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20a%20day%20in%20my%20life%20is%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c94e6d28-0e55-48b1-ae58-1166738f34d4%5C%22%3EI%20wake%20up%20naturally%20around%206%20or%206%3A30%20a.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wake%20up%20when%20my%20body%20is%20ready%2C%20typically%20around%206%20or%206%3A30.%20It%20might%20be%20five%20or%2010%20minutes%20before%20I%20hop%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20check%20email%20quickly%20to%20see%20if%20there's%20anything%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20not%2C%20I%20stay%20off%20the%20machine%20unless%20I've%20got%20something%20on%20deadline.%20I%20get%20dressed%2C%20check%20the%20tires%20on%20my%20bike%2C%20and%20organize%20my%20belongings.%20While%20I'm%20doing%20those%20somewhat%20mindless%20tasks%2C%20I%20let%20myself%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20happens%20first%20thing%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20where%20all%20the%20unraveled%20pieces%20of%20information%20from%20the%20night%20before%20feel%20ready%20to%20be%20integrated.%20It's%20a%20remarkably%20productive%20period%20of%20time%20for%20me%20to%20find%20clarity%2C%20think%20broadly%2C%20and%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20eat%20breakfast%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20shower%20at%20home%2C%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flyft-ceo-david-risher-cycling-matcha-undercover-drive-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20bike%2030%20minutes%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20work%20and%20have%20a%20shower%20at%20my%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226eb9a02f-e68d-4afa-85a0-8fa14146ffe0%5C%22%3EI%20ride%20my%20bike%20to%20the%20office%20around%207%3A30%20or%208%20a.m.%20and%20don't%20structure%20my%20day%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hit%20the%20office%20around%207%3A30%20or%208%20a.m.%20Before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20we%20had%20over%2020%20people%20in%20the%20office%3B%20now%2C%20most%20of%20our%20staff%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-manager-commuting-return-office-day-care-childcare-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20are%20hybrid.%20Unless%20I'm%20out%20of%20town%2C%20I%20go%20to%20the%20office%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20taking%20a%20shower%2C%20I%20switch%20gears%20from%20undisciplined%20thoughts%20to%20the%20highest-priority%20task%20of%20the%20day%2C%20whether%20that's%20creating%20a%20presentation%2C%20building%20a%20spreadsheet%2C%20or%20simply%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22edc4a312-bed0-4a70-a564-30a312e63c7e%5C%22%3EMeetings%20commence%20at%209%3A30%20a.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20the%20type%20to%20be%20super%20regimented%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20very%20good%20at%20time%20management.%20I%20run%20a%20whole%20lot%20more%20on%20enthusiasm%20than%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20keep%20track%20of%20everything%20throughout%20the%20day%20by%20using%20index%20cards.%20I%20scribble%20down%20words%2C%20little%20pictures%2C%20reminders%2C%20charts%2C%20or%20whatever%20else%20I%20need%20to%20remember.%20It's%20a%20fast%20and%20flexible%20way%20for%20me%20to%20stay%20organized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2267111a2e-9a48-4b6d-891c-24aaa24b2597%5C%22%3EI%20take%20midday%20naps%20in%20a%20sleep%20pod%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20enthusiasm%20keeps%20me%20going%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20infrequent%20that%2C%20in%20the%20afternoon%2C%20I%20start%20dragging.%20I%20feel%20it%20physically%2C%20as%20if%20magnets%20are%20pulling%20me%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20can%2C%20I'll%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-not-crash-2015-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etake%20a%20nap%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20cot%20I've%20set%20up%20in%20my%20closet.%20Sometimes%20I%20look%20for%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20schedule%2C%20or%20I%20just%20cancel%20things.%20I%20let%20my%20body%20take%20control%20and%20don't%20set%20an%20alarm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20knows%20I%20nap.%20I%20used%20to%20stick%20a%20Post-it%20on%20the%20closed%20door%2C%20saying%20%26quot%3BThe%20old%20man%20is%20sleeping.%26quot%3B%3C%