e%20end%20goal%20may%20be%20the%20same%20as%20more%20typical%20industrial%20policy%20%E2%80%94%20supporting%20certain%20sectors%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20being%20performed%20on%20a%20micro%20level.%20Trump%20has%20also%20been%20critical%20of%20policies%20with%20the%20same%20end%20in%20mind.%20Back%20in%20March%2C%20he%20told%20Congress%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20rid%20of%26quot%3B%20the%20CHIPS%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20Intel%20has%20been%20underperforming%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20of%20anyone%20who%20feels%20that%20if%20Intel%20continued%20to%20underperform%2C%20there%20was%20a%20risk%20of%20taking%20the%20entire%20technology%20sector%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartnick%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20seen%20a%20rationale%20for%20how%20these%20particular%20companies%20were%20selected%2C%20how%20these%20particular%20industries%20were%20selected%2C%20how%20the%20valuations%20were%20reached.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20may%20have%20determined%20that%20the%20US%20can't%20win%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-us-china-entering-new-cold-war-amid-coronavirus-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexistential%20battle%20with%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20protect%20its%20economic%20priorities%20with%20the%20regular%20tools%20in%20the%20toolbox.%20William%20Henagan%2C%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20says%20those%20instruments%20have%20proven%20effective%20in%20the%20past%20because%20of%20the%20size%20of%20America's%20economy%20and%20the%20critical%20role%20the%20US%20dollar%20plays%20in%20global%20finance.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20White%20House%20thinks%20throwing%20around%20our%20national%20weight%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20achieve%20their%20desired%20outcomes%20is%20an%20eyebrow-raising%20sign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20basically%20been%20able%20to%20use%20restrictive%20enforcement%20tools%20to%20achieve%20international%20policy%20outcomes%20that%20we%20were%20interested%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Henagan%20says.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20no%20longer%20sufficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20White%20House%20official%20tells%20me%20there's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20much%26quot%3B%20a%20logic%20to%20what%20the%20administration%20is%20doing%20in%20taking%20equity%20stakes%20in%20strategic%20industries%20and%20sectors.%20%26quot%3BThe%20point%20with%20the%20equity%20stakes%20is%20that%20it's%20a%20tool%20that%20other%20countries%20have%20used%20with%20various%20degrees%20of%20success%2C%20but%20we're%20not%20indiscriminately%20trying%20to%20take%20equity%20stakes%20in%20everyone%2C%20in%20anything.%20We%20see%20it%20as%20a%20very%20powerful%20tool%20that%20we're%20using%20very%20judiciously%20in%20very%20specific%20sectors%20for%20very%20specific%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20say.%20Losing%20Intel%2C%20for%20example%2C%20would%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Basymmetric%20blow%26quot%3B%20to%20America's%20national%20and%20economic%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20equity%20stakes%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Brounding%20error%26quot%3B%20compared%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-third-quarter-economy-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrillions%20of%20dollars%20of%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20affected%20by%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20are%20very%20unequivocally%20free-market%20or%20pro-capitalist%20policymaking%26quot%3B%20activities%2C%20the%20official%20says%2C%20pointing%20to%20tax%20cuts%20and%20deregulation%2C%20among%20other%20moves.%20But%20they%20are%20an%20acknowledgment%20that%20the%20White%20House%20feels%20the%20free%20market%20has%20fallen%20short%20in%20shoring%20up%20these%20critical%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20motivation%20for%20taking%20stakes%20in%20companies%20may%20be%20clear-ish%2C%20the%20execution%20is%20not%2C%20nor%20are%20the%20potential%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20very%20little%20about%20the%20other%20rights%20that%20are%20associated%20with%20these%20deals%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartnick%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20predict%20exactly%20how%20the%20government%20will%20wield%20its%20equity-derived%20power.%20How%20will%20these%20stakes%20dilute%20the%20rights%20of%20existing%20shareholders%3F%20And%20what%20happens%20if%20the%20US%20government's%20interests%20don't%20align%20with%20those%20of%20other%20stockholders%3F%20Will%20the%20company%20feel%20compelled%20to%20follow%20through%20on%20what%20the%20government%20says%2C%20regardless%3F%20How%20exactly%20will%20the%20terms%20of%20these%20deals%20work%3F%20And%20even%20if%20the%20government%20doesn't%20use%20the%20hard%20power%20of%20its%20vote%20shares%2C%20it%20can%20use%20soft%20power%20to%20keep%20companies%20it's%20invested%20in%20from%20stepping%20out%20of%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government's%20Intel%20investment%20will%20be%20passive%2C%20meaning%20it%20gets%20no%20board%20representation%20or%20other%20governance%20rights%2C%20and%20it's%20agreed%20to%20vote%20with%20the%20company's%20board%20of%20directors%20%E2%80%94%20with%20limited%20exceptions.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20MP%20Materials%20agreement%2C%20the%20company%20isn't%20allowed%20to%20nominate%20any%20board%20members%20who%20are%20not%20US%20citizens%20without%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense's%20consent.%20However%2C%20the%20government%20will%20generally%20vote%20with%20the%20company's%20board%2C%20with%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20American%20capitalism%20is%20generally%20supposed%20to%20work%20is%20that%20money%20flows%20to%20companies%20that%20are%20doing%20the%20best%20job%20of%20utilizing%20it.%20The%20whole%20idea%20is%20that%20market%20capital%20allocation%20is%20designed%20to%20separate%20the%20wheat%20from%20the%20chaff.%20These%20stakes%20may%20distort%20that%20%E2%80%94%20the%20government%20is%20choosing%20which%20specific%20firms%20it%20wants%20to%20come%20out%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20if%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20going%20about%20throwing%20around%20money%2C%20rather%20than%20businesses%20focusing%20on%20making%20the%20best%20products%20and%20services%20possible%2C%20they%20may%20turn%20their%20attention%20to%20currying%20favor%20with%20the%20president.%20Whether%20or%20not%20this%20%3Cem%3Eis%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecrony%20capitalism%20or%20merely%20appears%20to%20be%20doesn't%20really%20matter.%20If%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-dei-tariffs-taxes-business-uncertainty-scaredy-cat-capitalism-anxiety-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexecutives%20make%20the%20calculation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it's%20much%20better%20to%20be%20on%20Trump's%20good%20side%20than%20his%20bad%20side%2C%20they%20may%20fall%20in%20line%20preemptively.%20The%20competition%20isn't%20for%20customers%2C%20market%20share%2C%20or%20innovation%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20for%20the%20president's%20affection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20the%20business%20of%20running%20private%20companies%20from%20the%20Oval%20Office%2C%20the%20White%20House%20official%20tells%20me%2C%20but%20the%20point%20is%20for%20the%20government%20to%20have%20some%20sway.%20%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20the%20intent%20wasn't%20for%20us%20to%20take%20an%20equity%20stake%20in%20Intel%20and%20then%20they%20just%20close%20down%20their%20Ohio%20foundry%20and%20ship%20it%20off%20to%20Taiwan%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20says.%20The%20hope%20is%20there's%20an%20%26quot%3Boverlap%26quot%3B%20between%20what's%20best%20for%20companies%20and%20best%20for%20American%20economic%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Kennedy%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20in%20Chinese%20business%20and%20economics%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20in%20an%20economy%20as%20vast%20and%20varied%20as%20America's%2C%20Washington's%20power%20is%20relatively%20limited%2C%20and%20this%20activity%20could%20be%20just%20a%20%26quot%3Bminor%20nuisance%26quot%3B%20to%20industry.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20there%20are%20more%20cases%2C%20then%20it%20will%20begin%20to%20affect%20the%20decision-making%20of%20businesses%20and%20will%20increasingly%20orient%20them%20to%20think%20about%20how%20they%20should%20do%20business%20in%20a%20way%20that%20benefits%20the%20current%20administration%20as%20opposed%20to%20what%20benefits%20their%20company%20or%20the%20US%20national%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20that%20that%20could%20have%20a%20distorting%20effect%20eventually.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20better%20if%20tech%20CEOs%20spend%20less%20time%20in%20DC%20and%20more%20time%20coming%20up%20with%20new%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Owen%20Zidar%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20public%20affairs%20at%20Princeton%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20every%20analyst%2C%20economist%2C%20and%20academic%20I%20spoke%20to%20for%20this%20story%20agreed%20that%20Trump's%20version%20of%20American%20state%20capitalism%20is%20more%20a%20reflection%20of%20where%20the%20US%20is%20going%20than%20where%20it%20has%20been.%20It's%20not%20the%20same%20as%20what%20China's%20doing%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20socialism%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20unconventional%20step%20further%20down%20the%20road%20that%20the%20US%20has%20been%20on%20for%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20issues%20such%20as%20antitrust%20enforcement%2C%20industrial%20policy%2C%20and%20tariffs%2C%20factions%20within%20both%20the%20Republican%20and%20Democratic%20parties%20are%20leaning%20more%20towards%20interventionism.%20Trump%20is%20being%20more%20obvious%20with%20his%20actions%20and%20intentions%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20a%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook-donald-trump-gift-apple-tariffs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETim%20Cook%20is%20showing%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20with%20a%20gold%20plaque.%20This%20is%20a%20situation%20where%20there's%20likely%20no%20backtracking.%20Other%20countries%20are%20reacting%20to%20America's%20inward%20turn%20as%20well%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-canada-economy-tariffs-trade-war-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanada%20is%20shoring%20up%20%3C%2Fa%3Eits%20domestic%20economy%2C%20and%20Europe%20is%20taking%20a%20corporatist%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20changes%20the%20political%20equilibrium%20in%20a%20way%20that%20other%20countries%20pursue%20similar%20policies.%20And%20we%20get%20away%20from%20the%20brand%20of%20capitalism%20that%20we%20were%20doing%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Lane%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20bad%20thing%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20previous%20consensus.%20Capitalism%20is%20increasingly%20unpopular%20in%20America%2C%20especially%20among%20young%20people%2C%20for%20a%20reason.%20For%20many%20Americans%2C%20the%20system%20isn't%20working.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20breeding%20inequality%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusinesses-cost-moving-supply-chains-out-china-trump-tariff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshipping%20jobs%20overseas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20making%20the%20overall%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-hidden-economic-crisis-personal-financial-chaos-prices-layoffs-jobs-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomy%20more%20precarious%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20public%20got%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20the%20fragility%20of%20our%20supply%20chains%20and%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20the%20just-in-time%2C%20globally%20distributed%20setup.%20Political%20leaders%20and%20policymakers%20aren't%20wrong%20to%20wonder%20if%20the%20state%20shouldn't%20take%20a%20heavier%20hand%20in%20shoring%20up%20important%20industries%2C%20supporting%20vital%20companies%2C%20and%20making%20investments%20where%20the%20private%20market%20might%20blanch%20at%20the%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20has%20indicated%20that%20more%20equity%20investments%20are%20likely%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20but%20the%20criteria%20for%20who%20it%20will%20pick%20are%20a%20black%20box.%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20entirely%20leave%20it%20up%20to%20the%20market%20to%20do%20whatever%20it%20wants%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20not%20a%20great%20approach%20to%20the%20economy.%20Neither%20is%2C%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BWho%20gets%20a%20leg%20up%20depends%20on%20how%20the%20president's%20feeling%20today.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3EIt's%20odd%20for%20Trump%20to%20seize%20the%20means%20of%20production%20a%20little%20bit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20this%20sort%20of%20ideological%20view%20that's%20now%20breaking%20down%20a%20bit%20because%20we've%20realized%20that%20what%20we've%20been%20doing%20isn't%20good%20enough%2C%20isn't%20adequate%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Robert%20Atkinson%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20president%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20and%20Innovation%20Foundation%2C%20a%20tech%20and%20science%20policy%20think%20tank.%20%26quot%3BI%20wish%20there%20was%20a%20sort%20of%20unified%20field%20theory%20for%20this%20in%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20motives%20are%20understandable%2C%20the%20mechanics%20are%20anything%20but.%20It's%20unclear%20how%20the%20US%20will%20exit%20these%20investments%2C%20or%2C%20once%20it%20does%2C%20how%20much%20money%20it%20will%20actually%20make.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20enormous%20federal%20budget%2C%20the%20return%20will%20be%20minimal.%20It%20pushes%20the%20global%20economy%20into%20new%20territory%2C%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20whether%20it's%20one%20the%20US%20will%20always%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20spent%20decades%2C%20under%20both%20Democrats%20and%20even%20more%20so%20under%20Republicans%2C%20criticizing%20certainly%20China%20and%20Russia%2C%20but%20also%20Italy%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20the%20UK%20on%20their%20use%20of%20these%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartnick%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20the%20US%20starts%20to%20go%20down%20that%20path%20as%20well%2C%20it%20will%20give%20not%20just%20our%20adversaries%2C%20but%20also%20our%20allies%2C%20even%20greater%20license%20to%20do%20the%20same.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-era-america-capitalism-socialist-trump-economy-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767604261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6954214e64858d02d2178b66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-era-america-capitalism-socialist-trump-economy-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20is%20having%20the%20government%20buy%20stakes%20directly%20in%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20going%20to%20change%20the%20way%20we%20all%20do%20business%20and%20reshape%20the%20economy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-era-america-capitalism-socialist-trump-economy-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Universal%20Music%20India%20to%20acquire%20minority%20stake%20in%20Excel%20Entertainment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767603921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2026-01%2F05%2Fthumb%2Ffeatur